history.content: I mean you can do the math given the size and percentage filled of both the class and the waitlist. You can follow the 10% rule: roughly 10% of a class tends to drop. With CS 70's difficulty, I wouldn't be surprised if that number is higher. Priority enrollment will definitely help. You can also use BerkeleyTime to view enrollment percentage over time throughout each phase, so you can use that to estimate too. Don't depend on them expanding, but I would assume there is a chance of that.

As an IEOR major trying to switch to EECS, I wanted to take CS70 next semester. I noticed that it usually fills up but I've also heard that they expand it. Currently, BerkeleyTime says it has 54% enrollment with a waitlist of 9%. As a non-EECS and non-L&S major, what are my chances of getting into CS70 if I enroll during Phase II? I have priority enrollment so I will have one of the earliest Phase II times. Thanks in advance for the help!!!
history.subject: Chances of getting into CS70 if I enroll in Phase II
